 BY LINUS CHIBUIKE PRESIDENT Muhammadu Buhari, on Thursday, commiserated with the General Overseer of the Redeemed Christian Church of God, Pastor Enoch Adeboye, over the death of his son. The President extended his deepest sympathies to the family of the renowned Pastor in a message through his Special Adviser on Media and Publicity, Femi Adesina. He also commiserated with members of the RCCG on the demise of the Assistant Pastor in charge of Region (Youth) 35, urging them to find comfort in the teachings of the Holy Scriptures that ‘those who have chosen to serve God faithfully will see Him as He is in eternity.’ “The President prays God Almighty to grant the departed rest in His everlasting kingdom and comfort grieving family, friends and associates,” Adesina said. Pastor Dare Adeboye was said to have died in his sleep on Wednesday, at the age of 42. He reportedly died in Eket, Akwa Ibom State, where he was based with his family. 